Model integration rules
- Define class ModelNew(Model) with identical __init__ and forward signatures. Reuse PyTorch layers/weights.
- Only call custom CUDA kernels on CUDA tensors; keep fallback to PyTorch ops when device != "cuda" or extension fails to build.
- Keep gradients out of scope (forward-only).
- Bias broadcasting: if bias is (Cout) or (Cout,1,1), index bias[co] in CUDA and add per-output channel.
- Ensure all tensors passed to kernels are contiguous.

Performance checklist
- Contiguous inputs/weights/bias (call .contiguous()).
- Reasonable launch params: 128–256 threads; grid: ceil(numel/threads) or one block per row for GEMV fusion.
- Coalesced IO; grid-stride or flat index mapping.
- Fuse activation and bias in the same kernel when it exactly matches the model to avoid extra memory passes.
- Avoid unnecessary synchronizations; use at::cuda::getCurrentCUDAStream() for launches.

