    - Unroll inner k loop if possible; ensure bounds checks; use __syncthreads.
  - For elementwise/reduction kernels:
    - Use 256–1024 threads/block depending on register pressure.
    - Use coalesced loads/stores; avoid divergence; consider warp reductions for LSE/softmax-like ops.

